text: Honda is a city in the Tolima Department in Colombia. In 2015, about 35,000 people lived there. The city was founded in 1539, and has city status since 1830. Together with Libano it is the seat of the Roman Catholic diocesese Libano-Honda. Category:Cities in Colombia Category:1530s establishments in the Spanish Empire Category:Tolima Department
title: Honda (Colombia)
